steps.description:
Recheck and adjust the tuning of each string after tuning all of the strings. Changing the tension on each string will affect the tuning of the other strings. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a9/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a9/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Continue tuning each of the strings until they are all in tune simultaneously. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/77/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/77/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Lightly touch your finger on the string directly over the 12th fret. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Verify on the tuner that the string is tuned exactly to G.{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fret the string directly behind the fret. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0b/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0b/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fret the string with the same pressure that you would ordinarily use while playing. Resist the temptation to press more firmly on the string. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9d/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9d/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Note the tuning on the electronic tuner. If this note is sharp (above the tone of the harmonic), then the string length from the nut to the bridge needs to be increased. If the fretted note is flat (below the tone of the harmonic), then the string length from the nut to the bridge needs to be decreased. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/76/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/76/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If the string length needs to be increased, turn the bridge saddle adjustment screw clockwise. If the string length needs to be decreased, turn the bridge saddle adjustment screw counterclockwise. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bb/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bb/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Determine how much to change the saddle adjustment based on how far out of tune the fretted note was. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5e/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5e/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Play the harmonic to verify that the string is still in tune after adjusting the bridge saddle location. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fret the string at the 12th fret and play the note. Observe whether this note is in tune, sharp or flat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Repeat the process until the note played with the string fingered at the 12th fret is the same and in tune with the harmonic played at the 12th fret. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Adjust-Intonation-on-Bass-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
